The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, August 01, 2004 				 Indal profit jumps 60% to Rs 41 cr
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, July 31: Indian Aluminium Company (Indal), an Aditya Birla group firm, has recorded the best-ever first-quarter performance with the net profit soaring to Rs 40.8 crore, up 60 per cent compared with the profit of Rs 25.5 crore in the corresponding period last year.																								The turnover of the company has also increased 8 per cent to Rs 410 crore against Rs 380.9 crore. Exports have risen again by 36 per cent to Rs 141 crore compared with Rs 103 crore.																								According to a company release, the first quarter performance has been the best-ever in terms of sales and profits, driven by fundamental improvement across all operating parametres.																								Some key factors which contributed to this were improved production from the Hirakud smelter, Belgaum alumina and Belur sheet plant, higher export volumes in sheet and speciality chemicals and efficiency improvements in the operations of primary smelting and downstream, it says.																								This apart, the gains from the first phase of expansions carried out in primary metal and captive power, alumina refineries and commissioning of coal mines are reflected in the first quarter performanc.																								The company said the pre-project activities on the second phase of expansion projects in alumina, aluminium and power generation, have commenced. 
